# Testing Rules

## Backend (pytest)

- Test files in `apps/api/tests/`, mirroring `src/app/` structure.
- Use `pytest-asyncio` with `@pytest.mark.asyncio` for async tests.
- Naming: `test_<unit>_<scenario>_<expected>` — e.g., `test_verify_signature_with_valid_hmac_returns_true`.
- Fixtures in `conftest.py` at the level they're used. Don't over-centralize.
- Mock external APIs (`httpx`, Anthropic, GitHub) with `pytest-httpx` or `respx`.
- **Don't test private functions directly.** Test through the public interface.

## What to test at each layer

| Layer | What |
|---|---|
| Parsers (diff, config) | Edge cases: empty, malformed, huge, unicode |
| Tool implementations | Normal case, error case, timeout, malicious input |
| Agent loop | With mocked Anthropic client returning pre-recorded responses |
| Pydantic schemas | Boundary validation (min/max, required fields) |
| Webhook handlers | Signature verification, event filtering, enqueuing |
| API routes | Auth, happy path, bad input returns 400, DB errors return 500 |
| DB models | Constraints, indexes, cascade behavior |

## Coverage targets

- Agent core (`apps/api/src/app/agent/`): **80%+ line coverage**.
- Webhook handlers: **90%+ line coverage** — these are security-critical.
- UI components: lighter, focus on logic and accessibility.

## Frontend (Vitest)

- Test files next to components: `FindingCard.test.tsx`.
- Use `@testing-library/react`. Query by accessible role/label, not by class or test ID (unless absolutely necessary).
- Mock TanStack Query with `@tanstack/react-query`'s testing utilities.
- For hooks, use `renderHook` from Testing Library.

## E2E (Playwright)

- Lives in `apps/web/e2e/`.
- Runs against a real API (test DB) in CI, not mocked.
- Happy-path scenarios only — unit tests cover the details.
- Keep under 10 tests; these are slow and flaky if over-used.

## Evals (separate from tests)

- Evals are NOT unit tests. They're probabilistic quality checks.
- Run on every prompt change via CI.
- Report precision/recall/FP rate, compare to baseline, gate merges.
- Never run evals on every push — they cost real money. Label-gated: add `prompt-change` label to trigger.

## What not to test

- Third-party library internals (FastAPI's request parsing, SQLAlchemy's query builder).
- Trivial getters/setters.
- Auto-generated code.

## Tests in PRs

- Every bug fix PR includes a regression test.
- Every new feature PR includes tests before merging.
- A PR that decreases coverage > 2% needs justification in the description.
